  "text": "## Kafka Consumer Offset Management Architecture\n\nApache Kafka implements a comprehensive consumer offset management system centered around the __consumer_offsets internal topic and the GroupCoordinator. Here are the key components:\n\n### 1. OffsetAndMetadata Storage\nTwo implementations exist:\n- **Client-side (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/OffsetAndMetadata.java)**: Contains consumer-facing offset and metadata, with support for leader epoch.\n- **Coordinator-side (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/OffsetAndMetadata.java)**: Stores server-side offset metadata with commit timestamps and expiration tracking.\n\nOffsets are stored in the compacted __consumer_offsets topic as defined in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/internals/Topic.java, which is used for log compaction to maintain only the latest offset commits.\n\n### 2. GroupCoordinator Interface and Implementation\nThe core coordinator system:\n- **GroupCoordinator.java** (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/): Defines the interface for offset commit, fetch, and delete operations.\n- **GroupCoordinatorService.java**: Implements the GroupCoordinator interface, orchestrating offset management across multiple coordinator shards.\n- **GroupCoordinatorShard.java**: Handles offset operations for a specific partition of the group metadata.\n\n### 3. Offset Commit Handler\nThe offset commit flow:\n1. Client sends OffsetCommitRequest (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetCommitRequest.java)\n2. KafkaApis.handleOffsetCommitRequest (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaApis.scala) routes to GroupCoordinator.commitOffsets()\n3. GroupCoordinatorService.commitOffsets() processes the request\n4. GroupCoordinatorShard.commitOffsets() persists offsets via OffsetMetadataManager\n5. OffsetAndMetadata objects are stored in __consumer_offsets topic for durability and log compaction\n\nThe CommitRequestManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CommitRequestManager.java) on the client side manages offset commit requests with retries and batching.\n\n### 4. OffsetFetch Request Processor\nThe offset fetch flow:\n1. Client sends OffsetFetchRequest (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/OffsetFetchRequest.java)\n2. KafkaApis.handleOffsetFetchRequest routes to GroupCoordinator.fetchOffsets()\n3. GroupCoordinatorService.fetchOffsets() retrieves stored offsets\n4. OffsetMetadataManager.fetchOffsets() retrieves from in-memory cache or compacted topic\n5. Response sent via OffsetFetchResponse\n\nThe CommitRequestManager.fetchOffsets() manages client-side offset fetch requests with support for committed offsets lookup.\n\n### 5. Offset Expiry and Compaction Logic\nOffset expiration is managed through:\n- **OffsetExpirationCondition.java** and **OffsetExpirationConditionImpl.java**: Define expiration policies based on commit timestamps.\n- **Group implementations** (ClassicGroup, ConsumerGroup, StreamsGroup) provide offsetExpirationCondition() to determine when offsets should expire.\n- **OffsetMetadataManager.removeExpiredOffsets()**: Removes expired offsets and produces tombstone records to the __consumer_offsets topic for log compaction.\n\nEach group type can customize expiration logic:\n- ClassicGroup: Uses commit timestamp for expiration\n- ConsumerGroup: Uses commit timestamp for expiration\n- StreamsGroup: Uses commit timestamp for expiration\n- ShareGroup: Does not support offset expiration\n\nOffsets are deleted via:\n- **GroupCoordinator.deleteOffsets()**: Explicit deletion via admin API\n- **OffsetMetadataManager.deleteOffsets()**: Produces delete tombstones for log compaction\n\nThe __consumer_offsets topic uses log compaction cleanup policy to maintain only the latest offset commit per group+topic+partition combination, automatically cleaning up stale offset records.\n\n### 6. Supporting Components\n- **OffsetCommitCallbackInvoker** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/OffsetCommitCallbackInvoker.java): Invokes callbacks after offset commits complete\n- **OffsetCommitMetricsManager** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/metrics/OffsetCommitMetricsManager.java): Tracks offset commit metrics\n- **ConsumerCoordinator** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerCoordinator.java): High-level consumer coordination including offset management\n\nThe architecture ensures reliable, durable offset storage with automatic cleanup and expiration of stale offsets through Kafka's log compaction mechanism."
}

